      • analyze

        public JAST analyze​(Context context)
        Analysis for a method declaration involves (1) creating a new method context (that records the return type; this is used in the analysis of the method body), (2) bumping up the offset (for instance methods), (3) declaring the formal parameters in the method context, and (4) analyzing the method's body.
        Specified by:
        analyze in class JAST
        Parameters:
        context - context in which names are resolved.
        Returns:
        the analyzed (and possibly rewritten) AST subtree.
